<node id="anger">
  <data key="d2">anger</data>
  <data key="d3">anger</data>
  <data key="d4">["anger"]</data>
  <data key="d5">[]</data>
  <data key="d6">passion</data>
  <data key="d7">Anger is another thing choice is not, since acts due to anger are not especially thought objects of choice.</data>
  <data key="d8">textual</data>
  <data key="d9">3</data>
  <data key="d10">[2]</data>
  <data key="d11">[{"note": "Aristotle says acts due to anger are thought less than any others objects of choice.", "passage_id": "ne.b3.s2.p4", "quote_excerpt": null, "support_type": "direct"}]</data>
  <data key="d12">approved</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
  <data key="d14">anger</data>
  <data key="d15">1</data>
  <data key="d16">["ne.b3.s2.p4"]</data>
  <data key="d17">["Aristotle says acts due to anger are thought less than any others objects of choice."]</data>
  <data key="d18">["direct"]</data>
</node>
<node id="appetite">
  <data key="d2">appetite</data>
  <data key="d3">appetite</data>
  <data key="d4">["appetite"]</data>
  <data key="d5">[]</data>
  <data key="d6">passion</data>
  <data key="d7">Appetite is one of the candidates Aristotle rejects as identical with choice.</data>
  <data key="d8">textual</data>
  <data key="d9">3</data>
  <data key="d10">[2]</data>
  <data key="d11">[{"note": "Aristotle says appetite is not the same as choice and can conflict with it.", "passage_id": "ne.b3.s2.p3", "quote_excerpt": null, "support_type": "direct"}]</data>
  <data key="d12">approved</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
  <data key="d14">appetite</data>
  <data key="d15">1</data>
  <data key="d16">["ne.b3.s2.p3"]</data>
  <data key="d17">["Aristotle says appetite is not the same as choice and can conflict with it."]</data>
  <data key="d18">["direct"]</data>
</node>
<node id="bodily-pleasures-and-pains">
  <data key="d2">bodily-pleasures-and-pains</data>
  <data key="d3">bodily pleasures</data>
  <data key="d4">["bodily pleasures"]</data>
  <data key="d5">["bodily pleasures and pains"]</data>
  <data key="d6">domain</data>
  <data key="d7">Book III narrows temperance and self-indulgence to bodily pleasures, especially those of touch.</data>
  <data key="d8">editorial_normalization</data>
  <data key="d9">3</data>
  <data key="d10">[10, 11]</data>
  <data key="d11">[{"note": "Aristotle says temperance must be concerned with bodily pleasures.", "passage_id": "ne.b3.s10.p2", "quote_excerpt": null, "support_type": "direct"}]</data>
  <data key="d12">approved</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
  <data key="d14">bodily pleasures</data>
  <data key="d15">1</data>
  <data key="d16">["ne.b3.s10.p2"]</data>
  <data key="d17">["Aristotle says temperance must be concerned with bodily pleasures."]</data>
  <data key="d18">["direct"]</data>
</node>
<node id="choice">
  <data key="d2">choice</data>
  <data key="d3">choice</data>
  <data key="d4">["choice"]</data>
  <data key="d5">[]</data>
  <data key="d6">action</data>
  <data key="d7">Choice is deliberate desire of what is in our power and shows character more precisely than bare action does.</data>
  <data key="d8">textual</data>
  <data key="d9">3</data>
  <data key="d10">[2, 3]</data>
  <data key="d11">[{"note": "Aristotle defines choice as deliberate desire of things in our own power.", "passage_id": "ne.b3.s3.p4", "quote_excerpt": null, "support_type": "direct"}]</data>
  <data key="d12">approved</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
  <data key="d14">choice</data>
  <data key="d15">1</data>
  <data key="d16">["ne.b3.s3.p4"]</data>
  <data key="d17">["Aristotle defines choice as deliberate desire of things in our own power."]</data>
  <data key="d18">["direct"]</data>
</node>
<node id="compulsion">
  <data key="d2">compulsion</data>
  <data key="d3">compulsion</data>
  <data key="d4">["under compulsion", "compulsory"]</data>
  <data key="d5">[]</data>
  <data key="d6">condition</data>
  <data key="d7">Compulsion describes cases where the moving principle is outside the agent and he contributes nothing.</data>
  <data key="d8">editorial_normalization</data>
  <data key="d9">3</data>
  <data key="d10">[1]</data>
  <data key="d11">[{"note": "Aristotle defines the compulsory by an external moving principle to which the agent contributes nothing.", "passage_id": "ne.b3.s1.p1", "quote_excerpt": null, "support_type": "direct"}]</data>
  <data key="d12">approved</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
  <data key="d14">compulsion</data>
  <data key="d15">1</data>
  <data key="d16">["ne.b3.s1.p1"]</data>
  <data key="d17">["Aristotle defines the compulsory by an external moving principle to which the agent contributes nothing."]</data>
  <data key="d18">["direct"]</data>
</node>
<node id="courage">
  <data key="d2">courage</data>
  <data key="d3">courage</data>
  <data key="d4">["courage"]</data>
  <data key="d5">[]</data>
  <data key="d6">virtue</data>
  <data key="d7">Courage is the mean with respect to fear and confidence, especially where noble danger and death are at stake.</data>
  <data key="d8">textual</data>
  <data key="d9">3</data>
  <data key="d10">[6, 7, 8, 9]</data>
  <data key="d11">[{"note": "Aristotle says courage is the mean with respect to things that inspire confidence or fear.", "passage_id": "ne.b3.s7.p3", "quote_excerpt": null, "support_type": "direct"}]</data>
  <data key="d12">approved</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
  <data key="d14">courage</data>
  <data key="d15">1</data>
  <data key="d16">["ne.b3.s7.p3"]</data>
  <data key="d17">["Aristotle says courage is the mean with respect to things that inspire confidence or fear."]</data>
  <data key="d18">["direct"]</data>
</node>
<node id="cowardice">
  <data key="d2">cowardice</data>
  <data key="d3">cowardice</data>
  <data key="d4">["coward"]</data>
  <data key="d5">["cowardice"]</data>
  <data key="d6">vice</data>
  <data key="d7">Cowardice is the excess of fear and lack of confidence opposed to courage.</data>
  <data key="d8">editorial_normalization</data>
  <data key="d9">3</data>
  <data key="d10">[7, 12]</data>
  <data key="d11">[{"note": "Aristotle describes the coward as exceeding in fear and lacking confidence.", "passage_id": "ne.b3.s7.p2", "quote_excerpt": null, "support_type": "direct"}]</data>
  <data key="d12">approved</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
  <data key="d14">cowardice</data>
  <data key="d15">1</data>
  <data key="d16">["ne.b3.s7.p2"]</data>
  <data key="d17">["Aristotle describes the coward as exceeding in fear and lacking confidence."]</data>
  <data key="d18">["direct"]</data>
</node>
<node id="deliberation">
  <data key="d2">deliberation</data>
  <data key="d3">deliberation</data>
  <data key="d4">["deliberation"]</data>
  <data key="d5">[]</data>
  <data key="d6">process</data>
  <data key="d7">Deliberation concerns what can be done by us and works through the means to an assumed end.</data>
  <data key="d8">textual</data>
  <data key="d9">3</data>
  <data key="d10">[3]</data>
  <data key="d11">[{"note": "Aristotle says deliberation is about means rather than ends and traces how an end is to be achieved.", "passage_id": "ne.b3.s3.p3", "quote_excerpt": null, "support_type": "direct"}]</data>
  <data key="d12">approved</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
  <data key="d14">deliberation</data>
  <data key="d15">1</data>
  <data key="d16">["ne.b3.s3.p3"]</data>
  <data key="d17">["Aristotle says deliberation is about means rather than ends and traces how an end is to be achieved."]</data>
  <data key="d18">["direct"]</data>
</node>
<node id="end">
  <data key="d2">end</data>
  <data key="d3">end</data>
  <data key="d4">["the end"]</data>
  <data key="d5">[]</data>
  <data key="d6">principle</data>
  <data key="d7">The end is what we wish for, while choice and deliberation address the means toward it.</data>
  <data key="d8">textual</data>
  <data key="d9">3</data>
  <data key="d10">[3, 4, 5]</data>
  <data key="d11">[{"note": "Aristotle says the end is what we wish for.", "passage_id": "ne.b3.s4.p1", "quote_excerpt": null, "support_type": "direct"}]</data>
  <data key="d12">approved</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
  <data key="d14">end</data>
  <data key="d15">1</data>
  <data key="d16">["ne.b3.s4.p1"]</data>
  <data key="d17">["Aristotle says the end is what we wish for."]</data>
  <data key="d18">["direct"]</data>
</node>
<node id="fear-and-confidence">
  <data key="d2">fear-and-confidence</data>
  <data key="d3">fear and confidence</data>
  <data key="d4">["fear and confidence", "things that inspire confidence or fear"]</data>
  <data key="d5">[]</data>
  <data key="d6">domain</data>
  <data key="d7">Fear and confidence are the sphere in which Aristotle distinguishes courage, rashness, and cowardice.</data>
  <data key="d8">textual</data>
  <data key="d9">3</data>
  <data key="d10">[6, 7, 9]</data>
  <data key="d11">[{"note": "Aristotle says courage is a mean with respect to what inspires confidence or fear.", "passage_id": "ne.b3.s7.p3", "quote_excerpt": null, "support_type": "direct"}]</data>
  <data key="d12">approved</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
  <data key="d14">fear and confidence</data>
  <data key="d15">1</data>
  <data key="d16">["ne.b3.s7.p3"]</data>
  <data key="d17">["Aristotle says courage is a mean with respect to what inspires confidence or fear."]</data>
  <data key="d18">["direct"]</data>
</node>
<node id="ignorance">
  <data key="d2">ignorance</data>
  <data key="d3">ignorance</data>
  <data key="d4">["ignorance"]</data>
  <data key="d5">[]</data>
  <data key="d6">condition</data>
  <data key="d7">Ignorance of the particulars can make an action involuntary when the action later brings pain and repentance.</data>
  <data key="d8">textual</data>
  <data key="d9">3</data>
  <data key="d10">[1]</data>
  <data key="d11">[{"note": "Aristotle treats ignorance of the circumstances and end of the action as what grounds involuntary action.", "passage_id": "ne.b3.s1.p9", "quote_excerpt": null, "support_type": "direct"}]</data>
  <data key="d12">approved</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
  <data key="d14">ignorance</data>
  <data key="d15">1</data>
  <data key="d16">["ne.b3.s1.p9"]</data>
  <data key="d17">["Aristotle treats ignorance of the circumstances and end of the action as what grounds involuntary action."]</data>
  <data key="d18">["direct"]</data>
</node>
<node id="involuntary-action">
  <data key="d2">involuntary-action</data>
  <data key="d3">the involuntary</data>
  <data key="d4">["the involuntary"]</data>
  <data key="d5">["involuntary action"]</data>
  <data key="d6">action</data>
  <data key="d7">The involuntary covers actions done under compulsion or owing to the relevant kind of ignorance.</data>
  <data key="d8">textual</data>
  <data key="d9">3</data>
  <data key="d10">[1]</data>
  <data key="d11">[{"note": "Aristotle opens by saying the involuntary is what takes place under compulsion or owing to ignorance.", "passage_id": "ne.b3.s1.p1", "quote_excerpt": null, "support_type": "direct"}]</data>
  <data key="d12">approved</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
  <data key="d14">the involuntary</data>
  <data key="d15">1</data>
  <data key="d16">["ne.b3.s1.p1"]</data>
  <data key="d17">["Aristotle opens by saying the involuntary is what takes place under compulsion or owing to ignorance."]</data>
  <data key="d18">["direct"]</data>
</node>
<node id="means">
  <data key="d2">means</data>
  <data key="d3">means</data>
  <data key="d4">["means"]</data>
  <data key="d5">[]</data>
  <data key="d6">principle</data>
  <data key="d7">Means are the doable steps through which an end is pursued and about which choice and deliberation are concerned.</data>
  <data key="d8">textual</data>
  <data key="d9">3</data>
  <data key="d10">[2, 3, 5]</data>
  <data key="d11">[{"note": "Aristotle says we deliberate not about ends but about means.", "passage_id": "ne.b3.s3.p3", "quote_excerpt": null, "support_type": "direct"}]</data>
  <data key="d12">approved</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
  <data key="d14">means</data>
  <data key="d15">1</data>
  <data key="d16">["ne.b3.s3.p3"]</data>
  <data key="d17">["Aristotle says we deliberate not about ends but about means."]</data>
  <data key="d18">["direct"]</data>
</node>
<node id="opinion">
  <data key="d2">opinion</data>
  <data key="d3">opinion</data>
  <data key="d4">["opinion"]</data>
  <data key="d5">[]</data>
  <data key="d6">state</data>
  <data key="d7">Opinion differs from choice because it is assessed by truth and falsity rather than by moral quality.</data>
  <data key="d8">textual</data>
  <data key="d9">3</data>
  <data key="d10">[2]</data>
  <data key="d11">[{"note": "Aristotle distinguishes opinion from choice by its different objects and standards.", "passage_id": "ne.b3.s2.p6", "quote_excerpt": null, "support_type": "direct"}]</data>
  <data key="d12">approved</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
  <data key="d14">opinion</data>
  <data key="d15">1</data>
  <data key="d16">["ne.b3.s2.p6"]</data>
  <data key="d17">["Aristotle distinguishes opinion from choice by its different objects and standards."]</data>
  <data key="d18">["direct"]</data>
</node>
<node id="rashness">
  <data key="d2">rashness</data>
  <data key="d3">rashness</data>
  <data key="d4">["rash", "rash man"]</data>
  <data key="d5">["rashness"]</data>
  <data key="d6">vice</data>
  <data key="d7">Rashness is the excess in confidence that imitates courage without standing firm before what is truly terrible.</data>
  <data key="d8">editorial_normalization</data>
  <data key="d9">3</data>
  <data key="d10">[7]</data>
  <data key="d11">[{"note": "Aristotle names the excessive type rash and says he is a pretender to courage.", "passage_id": "ne.b3.s7.p2", "quote_excerpt": null, "support_type": "direct"}]</data>
  <data key="d12">approved</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
  <data key="d14">rashness</data>
  <data key="d15">1</data>
  <data key="d16">["ne.b3.s7.p2"]</data>
  <data key="d17">["Aristotle names the excessive type rash and says he is a pretender to courage."]</data>
  <data key="d18">["direct"]</data>
</node>
